Title: Learn Your Way: Reimagining textbooks with generative AI
Description: Textbooks are a cornerstone of education, but they have a fundamental limitation: they are a one-size-fits-all medium. The manual creation of textbooks demands significant human effort, and as a result they lack alternative perspectives, multiple formats and tailored variations that can make learning more effective and engaging. At Google, we‚Äôre exploring how we can use generative AI (GenAI) to automatically generate alternative representations or personalized examples, while preserving the integrity of the source material. What if students had the power to shape their own learning journey, exploring materials using various formats that fit their evolving needs? What if we could reimagine the textbook to be as unique as every learner?

Title: OpenAPI as a Single Source of Truth for APIs | Dochia CLI Blog
Description: By treating the OpenAPI specification as the single source of truth, teams can design APIs up front, generate always-accurate documentation, enforce contract-based tests, and even auto-produce client SDKs and server stubs across languages. This eliminates drift between code, tests, and docs, reduces duplication, and creates a shared foundation that streamlines collaboration throughout the API lifecycle.

Title: One Token to rule them all - obtaining Global Admin in every Entra ID tenant via Actor tokens
Description: While preparing for my Black Hat and DEF CON talks in July of this year, I found the most impactful Entra ID vulnerability that I will probably ever find. One that could have allowed me to compromise every Entra ID tenant in the world (except probably those in national cloud deployments). If you are an Entra ID admin reading this, yes that means complete access to your tenant. The vulnerability consisted of two components: undocumented impersonation tokens that Microsoft uses in their backend for service-to-service (S2S) communication, called ‚ÄúActor tokens‚Äù, and a critical vulnerability in the (legacy) Azure AD Graph API that did not properly validate the originating tenant, allowing these tokens to be used for cross-tenant access.
